'''Pellet Fuels Institute''' (PFI) is a North American [[trade organization]] that represents manufacturers, retailers and distributors of [[wood pellet]] fuel supplies and [[pellet stove|appliances]]. The PFI was formed in 1985 as the Fiber Fuels Institute.<ref>{{cite web|title=Who is PFI?|url=http://pelletheat.org/about-us/who-is-pfi/|publisher=PFI|accessdate=26 October 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029202140/http://pelletheat.org/about-us/who-is-pfi/|archivedate=29 October 2013|df=}}</ref>
Headquartered in [[Arlington, Virginia]], PFI maintains National Residential Pellet Fuel Standards,<ref>[http://apps1.eere.energy.gov/consumer/your_home/space_heating_cooling/index.cfm/mytopic=12570 “Wood and Pellet Heating,” U.S. Department of Energy]</ref> compiles and publishes data on sales and manufacturing output relating to the U.S. pellet fuel industry,<ref>[http://albany.bizjournals.com/albany/stories/2008/09/01/story14.html “Retailers say pellet stoves are hot item as customers flee from pricey oil heating,” The Business Review (Albany), August 29, 2008]</ref> hosts industry conferences,<ref>[http://www.aer-online.com/e107_plugins/content/content.php?content.454 “Pellet Fuels Institute Holds Annual Conference In July,” Alternative Energy Retailer, April 25, 2007]</ref> and provides outreach to consumers on the use of pellet fuel as an [[alternative energy]] thermal source.<ref>[http://www.alaskajournal.com/stories/120907/hom_20071209016.shtml “Pellet stoves: Economic, friendly alternative to fossil fuel,” Alaska Journal of Commerce, December 9, 2007]</ref>
