A '''quartz latite''' is a [[volcanic rock]] or fine grained [[intrusive rock]] equivalent to a [[latite]] with a [[phenocryst]] modal composition containing 5-20% [[quartz]]. Above 20% quartz, the rock would be classified as a [[rhyolite]]. It is the fine grained equivalent of a [[quartz monzonite]] containing approximately equal amounts of [[plagioclase]] and [[alkali feldspar]].<ref name=IUGS>[http://geology.csupomona.edu/alert/igneous/igclass.htm Classification of Igneous Rocks] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930000000/http://geology.csupomona.edu/alert/igneous/igclass.htm |date=September 30, 2011 }}</ref>

